[ Applause ]

00:11:35.510 --> 00:11:40.050
[ Pause ]

00:11:40.050 --> 00:11:43.380
&gt;&gt; Kwame Alexander: Good evening.

00:11:43.380 --> 00:11:46.590
I am just honored and
very grateful to be here.

00:11:46.590 --> 00:11:49.340
Thank you to Maria Rena [Assumed
Spelling], to Dr. Billington,

00:11:49.340 --> 00:11:53.850
to the National Book Festival
staff for this wonderful event,

00:11:53.850 --> 00:11:57.220
for 15 years of this
literary tradition.

00:11:57.220 --> 00:12:01.100
I grew up as a writer
here in this area.

00:12:01.100 --> 00:12:07.050
I became a poet in earnest across
the bridge in Arlington, Virginia.

00:12:07.050 --> 00:12:14.820
There was a woman, of course,
it always starts with a woman,

00:12:14.820 --> 00:12:19.790
that I had a crush on and I needed
to be able to convey that to her.

00:12:19.790 --> 00:12:24.610
And the only way I knew
- I wasn't very cool,

00:12:24.610 --> 00:12:26.800
I didn't get cool until recently.

00:12:26.800 --> 00:12:33.200 position:56%
[laughter] And so the only way I was
able to convey that I was interested

00:12:33.200 --> 00:12:37.580
in her was through a poem,
but not just any poem.

00:12:37.580 --> 00:12:40.000 position:56%
I wrote her a poem a day for a year.

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:54.670
[laughter] I am not a painter,
browns and blues we get along

00:12:54.670 --> 00:12:59.940
but we are not close, I am no Van
Gogh, but give me plain paper,

00:12:59.940 --> 00:13:05.440
a dull pencil, some Scotch
and I will hijack your curves.

00:13:08.510 --> 00:13:13.620
[ Applause ]

00:13:13.620 --> 00:13:17.870
Take your soul hostage,
paint a portrait so colorful

00:13:17.870 --> 00:13:21.680
and delicate you just may
have to cut off my ear.

00:13:21.680 --> 00:13:27.330
[laughter] And she married me.

00:13:28.510 --> 00:13:35.080
[ Applause ]

00:13:35.080 --> 00:13:36.380
I'm a poet.

00:13:36.380 --> 00:13:39.990
My life's work is taking
the human soul entire,

00:13:39.990 --> 00:13:45.090 position:56%
and like Langston Hughes said,
squeezing it like a lime or a lemon,

00:13:45.090 --> 00:13:48.500
drop by drop into atomic words.

00:13:48.500 --> 00:13:52.900
I am a poet, I write
to explore and explode.

00:13:52.900 --> 00:13:58.490
I write to dream a world that
does better, that knows better.

00:13:58.490 --> 00:14:05.350
My heart is here with you
tonight at seven p.m.,

00:14:05.350 --> 00:14:11.740
but my head is still some time
else at seven a.m. You see,

00:14:11.740 --> 00:14:16.940
24 hours ago my family and
I arrived from Singapore.

00:14:18.180 --> 00:14:21.540
And to just further
illustrate what that means,

00:14:21.540 --> 00:14:25.510
at two a.m. this morning I
hear music and dancing coming

00:14:25.510 --> 00:14:28.140
from my seven year old's room

00:14:28.140 --> 00:14:33.660
because she thinks it's two
o'clock p.m. We spent three weeks

00:14:33.660 --> 00:14:38.900
in Singapore eating black pepper
crab, drinking lime juice,

00:14:38.900 --> 00:14:43.580
and marveling at the greenest,
cleanest city we'd ever seen,

00:14:43.580 --> 00:14:47.410
but it wasn't just fun,
well at least not for me.

00:14:47.410 --> 00:14:51.980
It was work, I was there to write,
or rather to share my writing

00:14:51.980 --> 00:14:55.880
with 4,000 students at the
Singapore American School.

00:14:55.880 --> 00:15:00.240
Each day for three weeks
I did my normal thing.

00:15:00.240 --> 00:15:03.930
I talked about growing up in
a house with 10,000 books.

00:15:03.930 --> 00:15:07.800
I talked about wanting to be
cool in high school and figuring

00:15:07.800 --> 00:15:11.220
out that the answer to
that was playing tennis.

00:15:11.220 --> 00:15:14.930
[laughter] I talked about writing
my first poem for my mother

00:15:14.930 --> 00:15:18.520
on Mother's Day when I was 12,
the first line went something

00:15:18.520 --> 00:15:22.410
like this - Dear Mommy,
I hate Mother's Day.

00:15:22.410 --> 00:15:27.500
[laughter] I talked about writing a
love poem for a girl I had a crush

00:15:27.500 --> 00:15:31.090
on in college and then taking
an advanced poetry class

00:15:31.090 --> 00:15:32.500
with Nicki Giovanni
[Assumed Spelling]

00:15:32.500 --> 00:15:34.920
