00:20:56.850 --> 00:21:00.370
So who was this man?

00:21:00.370 --> 00:21:04.420 position:56%
Humboldt was born in 1769 in Prussia

00:21:04.420 --> 00:21:08.410
and he became the most
celebrated scientist of his age.

00:21:08.410 --> 00:21:12.210
His contemporaries thought
that he was the most famous man

00:21:12.210 --> 00:21:16.580
after Napoleon and they called
him the Shakespeare of Sciences.

00:21:16.580 --> 00:21:18.900
He was also brazenly adventurous.

00:21:18.900 --> 00:21:22.710
He went on a five-year
exploration of Latin America,

00:21:22.710 --> 00:21:28.920
and it was a voyage that
shaped his life, his thinking,

00:21:28.920 --> 00:21:32.460
and that made him legendary
across the world.

00:21:32.460 --> 00:21:37.020
He ventured deep into the
mysterious rainforest of Venezuela.

00:21:37.020 --> 00:21:40.540
He cross the Andes
from Bogota to Lima,

00:21:40.540 --> 00:21:43.600
climbing the highest
volcanoes in the world.

00:21:43.600 --> 00:21:49.080
And it was during this voyage that
he came up with a concept of nature

00:21:49.080 --> 00:21:52.700
that still very much
shapes our thinking today,

00:21:52.700 --> 00:21:55.910
the idea that nature
is a web of life.

00:21:55.910 --> 00:21:58.910
He described earth
as a living organism

00:21:58.910 --> 00:22:02.030
where everything is connected.

00:22:02.030 --> 00:22:08.960
He is also the forgotten
father of environmentalism.

00:22:08.960 --> 00:22:13.860
He warned of the devastating
environmental affects

00:22:13.860 --> 00:22:18.810
of monoculture irrigation
and deforestation.

00:22:18.810 --> 00:22:20.950
Amazingly, he predicted

00:22:20.950 --> 00:22:25.530
in 1800 harmful human
induced climate change.

00:22:25.530 --> 00:22:29.740
He brought together art,
the arts and the sciences.

00:22:29.740 --> 00:22:33.370
He said we had to feel
nature to understand nature.

00:22:33.370 --> 00:22:36.340
I could basically go on forever

00:22:36.340 --> 00:22:41.060
because he was an extraordinary
polymerase [Assumed Spelling],

00:22:41.060 --> 00:22:43.880
he was a genius polymerase
who crossed,

00:22:43.880 --> 00:22:46.380
who roamed across the disciplines.

00:22:46.380 --> 00:22:53.840
And he influenced scientists,
writers, poets and artists.

00:22:53.840 --> 00:22:58.550
Thomas Jefferson called him one of
the greatest ornaments of the age.

00:22:58.550 --> 00:23:00.990
Napoleon was jealous of him.

00:23:00.990 --> 00:23:04.960
