wanted to meet the President

00:23:47.020 --> 00:23:51.140
of the United States, Thomas
Jefferson, whom he greatly admired.

00:23:51.140 --> 00:23:56.590
He arrived in D.C. in early June
1804, and he was a very busy man.

00:23:56.590 --> 00:23:59.550
Everybody wanted to meet
the heroic explorer.

00:23:59.550 --> 00:24:02.110
James Madison hosted
a party for him.

00:24:02.110 --> 00:24:05.070
Jefferson hosted a party
at the White House for him.

00:24:05.070 --> 00:24:07.850
And he, of course, went to
The Library of Congress.

00:24:07.850 --> 00:24:11.330
He went here on the
4th of June, 1804.

00:24:11.330 --> 00:24:14.980
He also went to Mount Vernon,
spent the afternoon there,

00:24:14.980 --> 00:24:17.340
and then had dinner in Alexandria.

00:24:17.340 --> 00:24:20.410
And there's a wonderful
description of that evening

00:24:20.410 --> 00:24:23.570
by the artist, Charles
Willson Peale.

00:24:23.570 --> 00:24:27.240 position:56%
Basically what happened was they had
dinner in Alexandria, it was late,

00:24:27.240 --> 00:24:30.630
